# Admin Interface

## Menu Pages
- Use `add_menu_page()` for top-level menus
- Use `add_submenu_page()` for submenus
- Always check `current_user_can('manage_options')` or appropriate capability
- Use WordPress admin UI components (wp-admin styles)

## Settings API
Use WordPress Settings API for all settings:
- `register_setting()` with sanitization callback
- `add_settings_section()` to group related fields
- `add_settings_field()` for each field
- Use `settings_errors()` to display feedback messages

## Asset Loading
- Enqueue admin scripts/styles only on plugin pages
- Use `admin_enqueue_scripts` hook with page detection
- Check `$hook` parameter to load only where needed
- Use `wp_localize_script()` for passing data to JavaScript
